			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/28/but-can-we.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“But can we take a moment to consider the awfulness of Senator John McCain?” —<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/27/opinion/columnists/trumpcare-republican-moderates.html?smprod=nytcore-ipad&amp;smid=nytcore-ipad-share\">Paul Krugman</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-07-27T21:01:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/07/27/but-can-we.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/26/it-is-a.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>“It is a multitiered tower of political idiocy, a sublime monument to the moronic, a gaudy, gleaming, Ozymandian folly that leaves many of the president’s prior efforts in its shade.” —<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/26/opinion/donald-trump-jeff-sessions.html?smprod=nytcore-ipad&amp;smid=nytcore-ipad-share\">Ross Douthat</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-07-26T09:55:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/07/26/it-is-a.html"
		},
		
		{
			"id": "http://curt.micro.blog/2017/07/26/in-the-end.html",
	      	
			"content_html": "<p>In the end, McCain is reduced to merely an angry hypocrite. “[his] vote on Tuesday helped enable the broken process on health care that he came to the floor to decry” —<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/were-getting-nothing-done-mccain-in-emotional-return-laments-what-the-senate-has-become/2017/07/25/54d1c812-715e-11e7-8f39-eeb7d3a2d304_story.html\">WaPo</a></p>\n",
			"date_published": "2017-07-25T21:10:00-07:00",
			"url": "http://microblog.curtclifton.net/2017/07/25/in-the-end.html"
		},
		
		{
